description:
&lt;p&gt;Western Sussex Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust has a full-time vacancy for an experienced B6 Specialist Technician to work in the EBME (Electro-Biomedical Engineering) Department based at St. Richard&#39;s Hospital on the Chichester site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The EBME Department sits within MEMS (Medical Equipment Management Service), which includes Medical Devices, EBME maintenance departments &amp; Equipment Libraries on the Chichester &amp; Worthing sites, all providing a service to the three sites of the Trust - Chichester, Worthing &amp; Southlands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to provide comprehensive medical device maintenance, repair, commissioning &amp; management services for a wide range of medical devices, including specialist support of anaesthetic delivery units with monitoring, patient ventilators and respiratory support used in Critical Care, A&amp;E and NNU.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to provide the Trust with a quality level of technical support for medical devices , working with the EBME Manager &amp; MEMS team in their aim to ensure an efficient, appropriate &amp; safe service is available to the Trust and all patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameRizwan KhanJob titleEBME ManagerEmail addressrizwan.khan13@nhs.netTelephone number01903 205111 x85475&lt;/p&gt;
